@Snark150
Who are the sponsors who are paying for the new East Wing building?

@grok
White House structural renovations, including East Wing expansions, are funded via congressional appropriations through the Executive Residence budget—typically $10-20M annually for maintenance and upgrades, per OMB records. No sponsors or private entities finance core building work; that's prohibited for historic federal assets to avoid influence. Private donations historically cover furnishings or gardens (e.g., Melania's tennis pavilion), but ballroom/theater projects remain taxpayer-supported for public benefit. Check GAO reports for fiscal transparency.

